  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nEndpoint `/eth/v2/debug/beacon/states/<state_id>` does not correctly handle complex format of the Accept HTTP header.\r\n\r\nNimbus client has a similar functionality of checkpoint sync, during which it requests the latest state from the reliable Beacon Node API. However, the such request failes due to the following error:\r\n```\r\n{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"BAD_REQUEST: Unsupported endpoint version: v2\",\"stacktraces\":[]}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt appears that the problem is in the Accept header format that Nimbus client provides along with the request: `Accept: application/octet-stream,application/json;q=0.9`, which Lighthouse cannot parse correctly.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/nimbus-eth2/blob/13b264d509d48909bb354f85b879f22641723509/beacon_chain/spec/eth2_apis/rest_types.nim#L30\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nAll up to v2.1.5\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nBehaves like the endpoint does not exists.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nShould return an SSZ-formatted state, as requested by the Accept header.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nFor example, the issue is observed on the following public GBC Beacon Api endpoint, backed by the v2.1.5 Lighthouse nodes.\r\n```\r\n$ curl -H 'Accept: application/octet-stream,application/json;q=0.9' https://rpc-gbc.gnosischain.com/eth/v2/debug/beacon/states/head\r\n{\"code\":400,\"message\":\"BAD_REQUEST: Unsupported endpoint version: v2\",\"stacktraces\":[]}\r\n$ curl -H 'Accept: application/octet-stream' https://rpc-gbc.gnosischain.com/eth/v2/debug/beacon/states/head > state.ssz\r\n```\r\n",
