    "body": "Thanks for reporting!\r\n\r\nThis is a deficiency in our HTTP header parsing whereby we're parsing Accept headers in a very limited way, and ignoring the more complex Accept parsing defined in RFC7231: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7231#section-5.3.2.\r\n\r\nIt seems our HTTP library `warp` doesn't provide any functionality for parsing Accept headers, so we may need to do a bit of leg work.\r\n\r\nI found what looks like a great implementation in `actix_web` here: https://actix.rs/actix-web/actix_web/http/header/struct.Accept.html. Perhaps it would be possible to write some translation glue code in order to use that.\r\n\r\nAnother option would be to hand-roll our own implementation or create a crate specifically for this purpose to contribute back to the `warp` community. The `mime` crate does most of the heavy lifting, but lacks the comma splitting and q-factor prioritisation. I've sketched the beginning of what this might look like here: https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=bf69044d030d03df6da87eb6c1b4d61e. Although we shouldn't use `.split(',')` due to the presence of quoted strings (see: https://github.com/http-rs/http-types/issues/349).",
